  "body": "I forked Polygon mainnet and tried to send all ethers from account and got an error:\r\n\r\n`sender doesn't have enough funds to send tx. The max upfront cost is: 3690252990028643482 and the sender's account only has: 3690252390028643482`\r\n\r\nThere is definitely something wrong. Because I tried the same transaction at Polygon mainnet and it works as expected.\r\n\r\nHere my sample code with ethers.js\r\n\r\n```\r\nprovider\r\n        .getBalance(w.address)\r\n        .then((b) =>\r\n          w.connect(provider).sendTransaction({\r\n            to: sponsorAddress,\r\n            value: b.sub(parseUnits(\"600\", \"gwei\").mul(21_000)),\r\n            gasPrice: parseUnits(\"600\", \"gwei\"),\r\n          })\r\n        )\r\n        .then((tx) => tx.wait())\r\n        .then((rc) => [w.address, rc.transactionHash])\r\n```",
